Package io.artframework

Interface Result

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CombinedResult, FutureResult, TargetResult<TTarget,​TContext>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultCombinedResult, DefaultFutureResult, DefaultResult, DefaultTargetResult
    public interface Result
    The Result wraps the result status and additional messages. It is immutable, thread safe and does not return any null values.

      • success

        default boolean success()
        Returns true if the result is a success.

        This means that all requirement checks were successful or all actions have been executed.

        An EMPTY result status will also be a success. A non success (false) does not automatically mean that there was an error. A requirement for example can return a failure if a check failed or an error if a exception or some kind of error occurred. Use the error() method to check if there were actually any errors.

        This is the same as ResultStatus.isSuccess().

        Returns:
        true if the result is a success

      • failure

        default boolean failure()
        Returns true if the result is a failure.

        This is the direct opposite to success().

        Returns:
        true if the result is a failure

      • error

        default boolean error()
        Returns true if the result is in an error state.

        This means that one of the called checks thru an exception or encountered some other kind of error. success() will always be false if there were any errors.

        This is the same as ResultStatus.isError().

        Returns:
        true if an error occured

      • status

        ResultStatus status()
        Gets the status of this result. This is never null.
        Returns:
        the status of this result that is never null
        See Also:
        for more details on the result status codes

      • messages

        java.lang.String[] messages()
        Gets all additional messages of this result.

        These could be error messages or just informative messages that should be send to the user.

        Returns:
        a list of messages that is never null but may be empty

      • combine

        default CombinedResult combine​(Result result)
        Combines this result with the given result returning a new combined result.

        This will use the ResultStatus.combine(ResultStatus) method to combine the two result statuses and then merge the messages. Duplicate messages will be omitted.

        Parameters:
        result - the result to combine with this result
        Returns:
        the new combined result
